==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|fr|solénoïde}}, from {{der|en|grc|σωληνοειδής}} (from {{m|grc|σωλήν||channel, pipe}} + {{m|grc|-ειδής}}; see {{m|en|-oid}}).<ref>{{R:Etymonline}}</ref>

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|physics}} A [[coil]] of [[wire]] that acts as a [[magnet]] when an [[electric current]] flows through it.
# {{lb|en|engineering}} An [[electromechanical]] device consisting of such a coil containing a [[metal]] [[core]], the movement of which is controlled by the current.
# {{lb|en|electronics}} An electromechanical [[switch]] controlled by a solenoid; solenoid switch, [[relay]].
# {{lb|en|meteorology}} The region of intersection between [[isobaric]] and [[isopycnal]] surfaces.

